The article discusses a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Obama in June 2009. The memorandum aims to achieve greater equality for LGBT Americans serving in the federal government by extending benefits to same-sex partners of federal employees. The President acknowledges the discrimination faced by same-sex couples and expresses support for the repeal of the Defense of Marriage Act. He also announces his support for the Domestic Partners Benefits and Obligations Act of 2009, which seeks to provide same-sex partners of federal employees with the same benefits enjoyed by opposite-sex spouses. The President emphasizes that extending equal benefits is not only the right thing to do but also sound economic policy. The article concludes by stating that through these measures, the principles upon which the nation was founded will be advanced and the Union will be perfected.